description:
&lt;p&gt;Want to work for an OUTSTANDING Mental Health Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Community Mental Health Team for Older People services is looking to recruit an experienced Occupational Therapist (OT). This is a great opportunity for an OT who has either a physical or a mental health background.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OT is an integral part of the community service involving working within a multidisciplinary team. The OT will complete functional and specialist OT assessments to ensure that the physical and mental health needs are recognised and addressed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The OT interventions are OT specific and generic dependent on an individual’s needs. Some examples are; sleep hygiene, pain management, confidence-building, mindfulness, anxiety management, increasing access to valued occupations in the community and the use of technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The older people’s Occupational Therapy service is very supportive, employing over 50 experienced OT staff across the county wide service. All with a vast knowledge and skills base to network with and learn from. Opportunities available for CPD events and external training, supervision and appraisal will be provided by the band 7 OT to support continued development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The community role would be based in Colne House in Watford. The core hours for the team are Monday to Friday 9-5, we may be able to offer an alternative pattern, or flexible working - please contact Amanda Stratford 07775546850 if you would like to discuss possible options.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;All staff should comply with the Trusts’ Anti-Discriminatory Statement, Employee Charter, Trust Policies and Procedures, Code of Conduct and Equality and Diversity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda Stratford Head Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07775546850 or amanda.stratford1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tracy corneliusdove Head Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07747090803 or tracy.corneliusdove@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
